50.97	Battle_of_Salamis	Battle of Salamis	The Battle of Salamis was fought between an Alliance of Greek city-states and the Persian Empire in September 480 BCE, in the straits between the mainland and Salamis, an island in the Saronic Gulf near Athens. It marked the high-point of the second Persian invasion of Greece which had begun in 480 BCE.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ea/Salamis.png/300px-Salamis.png
